The defendant William Randal Wuorenma was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. William Randal Wuorenma is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • William Randal Wuorenma was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle. ADA:  Megan E. Kelly   DF ATTY:  Joseph Robert Caton   DF:  William Randal Wuorenma appeared. Case called at 3:58 p.m. Court notes this is the date and time set for a PTC but there is a resolution. ADA Kelly recites agreement. State is in compliance with victims rights.   Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads GUILTY to Ct 1  Possess Drug Paraphernalia  in 16CM51. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1 Possess Drug Paraphernalia  in 16CM51 . On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 2 in 16CM51. Bond on file.

  It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO ABUSIVE CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations,   Amanda C.   The term "abusive contact" is hereby defined as a verbal assault or an intentional infliction of or threat to inflict physical pain, physical injury or illness, an impairment of physical condition, and /or sexual contact or sexual intercourse without consent.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ordered that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis Stats.
